---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="CV" description="Alfie McGlennon — climate risk, energy systems, and applied ML.">
  <div class="cv-top">
    <h1>CV</h1>
    <a href="/Alfie_McGlennon_CV.pdf" class="cv-pdf-icon" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Download PDF">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 32 32" width="40" height="40" fill="none">
        <rect x="4" y="2" width="24" height="28" rx="2" fill="var(--bg-card)" stroke="var(--border)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <path d="M10 18h3.5v-4h2v4H19l-4.5 5-4.5-5z" fill="var(--text-muted)"/>
        <text x="16" y="13" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" font-weight="700" font-family="var(--font-mono)" fill="var(--accent)">PDF</text>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="cv-layout">
    <aside class="cv-sidebar">
      <nav>
        <a href="#overview" class="active">Overview</a>
        <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="#education">Education</a>
        <a href="#skills">Skills</a>
        <a href="#experience">Experience</a>
        <a href="#other">Other</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <div class="cv-main">

      <section id="overview" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <dl class="cv-overview">
          <dt>Name</dt>
          <dd>Alfie McGlennon</dd>

          <dt>Label</dt>
          <dd>Climate Risk & Applied ML</dd>

          <dt>Email</dt>
          <dd><a href="mailto:alfie.mcglennon@outlook.com">alfie.mcglennon@outlook.com</a></dd>

          <dt>Location</dt>
          <dd>Reading, UK</dd>

          <dt>Url</dt>
          <dd><a href="https://alfiemcglennon.github.io">alfiemcglennon.github.io</a></dd>

          <dt>Summary</dt>
          <dd>
            MSc student in Climate Change and AI at the University of Reading.
            Research focus on compound climate extremes and their implications for
            reinsurance and catastrophe modelling. I build applied tools that go
            beyond standard ML coursework: a validated DC power flow model of the
            GB transmission network running in the browser, and reinforcement
            learning agents trained to dispatch the national grid. Experienced with
            large-scale climate datasets (ERA5, Berkeley Earth), interactive
            visualisation, and GPU-accelerated training on HPC infrastructure.
          </dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section id="projects" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Projects</h2>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>GB Grid Scenario Tool</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Interactive browser-based DC power flow for GB transmission constraints</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Built a 27-zone DC power flow model of the GB electricity network from NESO open data, validated against published boundary transfers (B6F within 2%)</li>
              <li>Implemented LP-optimal dispatch using HiGHS compiled to WebAssembly, solving constrained dispatch in ~10ms client-side</li>
              <li>Integrated ERA5 weather climatology (140k hours, 27 zones) for wind, solar, and demand scenario generation</li>
              <li>Tested 16 network configurations across 4 resolutions, 3 dispatch methods, and 2 interconnector models</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cv-project-links">
              <a href="https://alfiemcglennon.github.io/gb-grid-tool/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live demo</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/AlfieMcGlennon/gb-grid-tool" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source</a>
              <a href="/blog/building-gb-grid-tool/">Write-up</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>RL Grid Dispatch</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Reinforcement learning agents for network-constrained power dispatch</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Trained PPO agents (Stable-Baselines3) on 9 years of hourly generation, demand, and weather data on HPC GPU cluster</li>
              <li>Designed and compared 4 reward functions across MLP and CNN architectures (448k parameters, 72 ERA5 weather channels)</li>
              <li>Best agent achieved +12.8% vs NESO dispatch cost with emissions 16% lower than cost-only baseline</li>
              <li>Identified action-space bottleneck: spatial CNN observations couldn't improve dispatch without topology-aware actions</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cv-project-links">
              <a href="/blog/rl-grid-dispatch-baseline/">Write-up</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2025</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>City Climate Bars & Stripes</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Interactive web app for city-level temperature visualisation</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Processed multi-decadal Berkeley Earth gridded temperature data for city-level climate stripe visualisations</li>
              <li>Built data pipeline in Python, frontend in D3.js with seasonal and annual rendering modes</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="cv-project-links">
              <a href="https://alfiemcglennon.github.io/city-climate-stripes/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live demo</a>
              <a href="https://github.com/AlfieMcGlennon/city-climate-stripes" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source</a>
              <a href="/blog/city-climate-stripes/">Write-up</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>Climate Playbook</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Interactive climate education and analytics platform</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Designing an interactive platform spanning KS1-KS5 and adult learners, grounded in physically realistic climate representations</li>
              <li>Building uncertainty-aware visualisations and simplified modelling tools using ERA5 reanalysis data</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="education" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Education</h2>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2025 – 2026</span>
            <span class="cv-location">Reading, UK</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>MSc Climate Change and Artificial Intelligence</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">University of Reading</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Dissertation: Compound climate extremes — frameworks for correlated hazard prediction across Europe</li>
              <li>Modules: Applied Data Science with Python, AI and Machine Learning, Data Science and Climate Services</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2021 – 2025</span>
            <span class="cv-location">Reading, UK</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>BSc Meteorology and Climate (2:1)</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">University of Reading</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Dissertation: Investigating an Equilibrium Approximation for the Bowen Ratio (First Class)</li>
              <li>Key modules: Data Science and Climate Services, Numerical Modelling, Boundary Layer Meteorology</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2021</span>
            <span class="cv-location">Wokingham</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>A-Levels</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">The Forest School</p>
            <p class="cv-inline">Mathematics (A), Geography (A), Physics (B)</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="skills" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Skills</h2>
        <div class="cv-skills-grid">
          <div>
            <h3>Programming & ML</h3>
            <p>Python (pandas, NumPy, matplotlib, PyTorch, Stable-Baselines3, scikit-learn), JavaScript, D3.js, SQL, Git</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Climate & Energy Data</h3>
            <p>ERA5 reanalysis, Berkeley Earth, NESO grid data, ETYS boundary transfers, gridded dataset processing, time-series analysis</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>ML & Modelling</h3>
            <p>Reinforcement learning (PPO), CNNs, feature engineering, DC power flow, linear programming (HiGHS), SHAP interpretation</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tools & Infrastructure</h3>
            <p>HPC GPU training (SLURM), WebAssembly, Astro, Power BI, JupyterLab, Gymnasium</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="experience" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Experience</h2>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2024.07</span>
            <span class="cv-location">Borehamwood</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>Data Analyst Intern</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Safestore</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Analysed customer data to identify behaviour trends and retention metrics</li>
              <li>Built data visualisations in Python (pandas, matplotlib, seaborn) to support business retention strategies</li>
              <li>Delivered presentations to senior management</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cv-entry">
          <div class="cv-entry-meta">
            <span class="cv-badge">2019 – Present</span>
            <span class="cv-location">Reading</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cv-entry-body">
            <h3>Swim Teacher (Level 2) & Lifeguard</h3>
            <p class="cv-org">Places Leisure</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Delivered structured instruction across all ability levels, adapting methods to diverse learning styles</li>
              <li>Maintained safety standards and incident response as part of a team</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="other" class="cv-block">
        <h2>Other</h2>
        <ul class="cv-other-list">
          <li>Triathlon competitor (10+ years, national level)</li>
          <li>Coach, TVTristars Triathlon Club (2018–2021)</li>
          <li>Swim instructor support, Bulmershe Leisure Centre and Reading Swim Club (2016–2019)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<script>
  // Scroll spy: highlight active sidebar link
  function initScrollSpy() {
    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.cv-block');
    const links = document.querySelectorAll('.cv-sidebar a');
    if (!sections.length || !links.length) return;

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          const id = entry.target.id;
          links.forEach(link => {
            link.classList.toggle('active', link.getAttribute('href') === `#${id}`);
          });
        }
      });
    }, {
      rootMargin: '-80px 0px -60% 0px',
      threshold: 0
    });

    sections.forEach(section => observer.observe(section));
  }

  initScrollSpy();
  document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', initScrollSpy);
</script>

<style>
  /* Widen the content area for sidebar layout */
  :global(.content-wrapper:has(.cv-layout)) {
    max-width: 960px;
  }

  .cv-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .cv-top h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cv-pdf-icon {
    position: absolute;
    right: 0;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .cv-pdf-icon:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* Two-column layout */
  .cv-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 150px 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Sidebar navigation with active bar */
  .cv-sidebar nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .cv-sidebar a {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .cv-sidebar a:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .cv-sidebar a.active {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-left-color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
  }

  /* Section blocks */
  .cv-block {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cv-block h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Overview key-value pairs */
  .cv-overview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr;
    gap: 0.6rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .cv-overview dt {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .cv-overview dd {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .cv-overview dd a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* Entry layout */
  .cv-entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cv-entry:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cv-entry-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    padding-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .cv-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 1px solid rgba(43, 124, 212, 0.25);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.2em 0.5em;
    white-space: nowrap;
    width: fit-content;
  }

  .cv-location {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .cv-entry-body h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.15rem 0;
  }

  .cv-org {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cv-inline {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cv-entry-body ul {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cv-entry-body li {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Project links — these get accent colors */
  .cv-project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .cv-project-links a {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .cv-project-links a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-sky);
  }

  /* Skills grid */
  .cv-skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cv-skills-grid h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .cv-skills-grid p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Other section */
  .cv-other-list {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cv-other-list li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cv-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .cv-sidebar {
      display: none;
    }

    .cv-block {
      padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    }

    .cv-overview {
      grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    }

    .cv-entry {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }

    .cv-entry-meta {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .cv-skills-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
